igd Koninkrijk","Cheshire, England":"Cheshire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Witham, Lincolnshire, England":"Lincolnshire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"1300–28 August 1369":"1300–28 August 1369","1300–1354":"1300–1354","1349–1369":"1349–1369","1300–1369":"1300–1369","1349":"1349","1369":"1369","28 August 1369":"28 August 1369","1300":"1300","1354":"1354","20 January 1354":"20 January 1354","1319":"1319","Alnwick, Northumberland, England":"Alnwick, Northumberland, England, United Kingdom","Cheshire, England":"Cheshire, England, United Kingdom","Witham, Lincolnshire, England":"Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Margaret","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["An extremely common given name from the Middle Ages onwards, derived via Old French <i>Marguerite</i> and Latin <i>Margarita</i> from Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>, from <i>margaron</i> ‘pearl’, a word ultimately of Hebrew origin. The name was always understood to mean ‘pearl’ throughout the Middle Ages. The first  St Margaret  was martyred at Antioch in Pisidia during the persecution instigated by the  Emperor Diocletian  in the early 4th century. However, there is some doubt about her name, as the same saint is venerated in the Orthodox Church as   Marina .  There were several other saintly bearers of the name, including St Margaret of Scotland (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."],"variants":[{"name":"Margareta","meanings":["From the Latin form of Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>.  See  <b>Margaret</b>   ."]},{"name":"Margaretta","meanings":["Formed from Margaret."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Margaret was born in 1300, in Cheshire, England, United Kingdom. She married John De Orreby Knt. in 1319, in Cheshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. She died on 28 August 1369, at the age of 69."},"et":{"1300–28 August 1369":"1300–28. august 1369","1300–1354":"1300–1354","1349–1369":"1349–1369","1300–1369":"1300–1369","1349":"1349","1369":"1369","28 August 1369":"28. august 1369","1300":"1300","1354":"1354","20 January 1354":"20. jaanuar 1354","1319":"1319","Alnwick, Northumberland, England":"Alnwick, Northumberland, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Cheshire, England":"Cheshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Witham, Lincolnshire, England":"Lincolnshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1300–28 August 1369":"1300–28. elokuuta 1369","1300–1354":"1300–1354","1349–1369":"1349–1369","1300–1369":"1300–1369","1349":"1349","1369":"1369","28 August 1369":"28. elokuuta 1369","1300":"1300","1354":"1354","20 January 1354":"20. tammikuuta 1354","1319":"1319","Alnwick, Northumberland, England":"Alnwick, Northumberland, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Cheshire, England":"Cheshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Witham, Lincolnshire, England":"Lincolnshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1300–28 August 1369":"1300–28 août 1369","1300–1354":"1300–1354","1349–1369":"1349–1369","1300–1369":"1300–1369","1349":"1349","1369":"1369","28 August 1369":"28 août 1369","1300":"1300","1354":"1354","20 January 1354":"20 janvier 1354","1319":"1319","Alnwick, Northumberland, England":"Alnwick, Northumberland, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Cheshire, England":"Cheshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Witham, Lincolnshire, England":"Lincolnshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Margaret est née en 1300, à Cheshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Elle a épousé John De Orreby Knt. en 1319, à Cheshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fille. Elle est décédée le 28 août 1369, à l’âge de 69 ans."},"de":{"1300–28 August 1369":"1300–28. August 